-- Best Buy Chairman Steps Down, to Explore Option for 20.1% Stake
-- B y   J a m e s   C a l l a n
-- 2012-06-07T13:16:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-07/best-buy-chairman-steps-down-to-explore-option-for-20-1-stake.html
Best Buy Co. said founder and
Chairman Richard Schulze resigned from the board and will
explore options for his 20.1 percent ownership stake in the
electronics retailer.  Schulze, 71, had previously planned to step down as
chairman after the 2012 annual meeting on June 21, and to
remain as a director through the 2013 meeting, Minneapolis-based
Best Buy said today in a statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Callan at 
 jcallan2@bloomberg.net  